## Catena dati END-TO-END (esempio: cliente carica file ‚Üí PC sala lo proietta)

1. **Speaker** (anon, no account) apre URL `https://app.../u/<upload_token>` (route `apps/web/src/features/upload-portal/`).
2. SPA chiama Supabase Storage TUS endpoint `/storage/v1/upload/resumable` con `bucketName: 'presentations'` e path `tenants/<tenant>/events/<event>/presentations/<id>/v<n>/<file>`.
3. Lato DB trigger `update_storage_used()` aggiorna quota tenant; trigger `check_storage_quota()` blocca se sopra limite.
4. SPA crea row `presentation_versions` con `status='ready'`, `sha256=<hash>`, `size_bytes=<n>`, `uploaded_via='speaker'`.
5. Trigger Realtime su `presentation_versions` ‚Üí channel `event:<event_id>` riceve `INSERT` ‚Üí admin/coordinator vedono nuova versione live.
6. Coordinator/admin clicca "Pubblica" ‚Üí UPDATE `presentations.current_version_id` ‚Üí trigger Realtime + trigger Broadcast su `room:<room_id>`.
7. **PC sala (Room Player)** browser anon su `https://app.../sala/<device_token>`:
   - Bootstrap iniziale via Edge Fn `room-player-bootstrap` ‚Üí sala + manifest + topic Broadcast UUID.
   - Subscribe `supabase.channel('room:<uuid>')` su evento `presentation_changed`.
   - Hook `useFileSync` riceve evento ‚Üí fetch nuova `presentation_version` ‚Üí calcola path ‚Üí File System Access API ‚Üí download streaming + verify SHA-256 ‚Üí notifica `synced`.
8. Tecnico in sala apre il file dal disco locale (PowerPoint/Keynote) ‚Äî file gia' presente, zero buffering.

## Catena LAN-only (Sprint M-N ‚Äî admin offline, sala offline, LAN attiva)

1. PC admin apre `apps/desktop` (Tauri 2). Setup ruolo `admin`, server Rust su `127.0.0.1:N`, mDNS publish `role=admin`.
2. PC sala apre `apps/desktop`. Setup ruolo `sala`, server Rust su `127.0.0.1:M`, mDNS publish `role=sala`.
3. SPA admin (modalita desktop): `cmd_discover_lan_pcs(role_filter='sala')` ritorna lista PC sala visibili.
4. Admin sceglie un PC sala ‚Üí genera codice 6 cifre ‚Üí Tauri command `pair_direct_lan({targetBaseUrl, ...})` ‚Üí POST `/functions/v1/pair-direct` sul server Rust della sala con codice + `device_name` + `event_id`.
5. Sala valida codice + persiste `device.json` con `pair_token_hash` + `network_mode='lan-online'`. Risponde `{device_token: "<sha256>"}`.
6. Admin riceve `device_token`, lo registra anche sul proprio admin-locale via `registerPairedDeviceOnAdminLocal({...})` (per fan-out futuro).
7. Admin carica file via Supabase Storage cloud OR via `/storage/v1/object/...` del proprio server Rust (modalita full-LAN).
8. `lan_push.rs` su admin ‚Üí POST `/events/file_added` su tutti i PC sala paired in `network_mode='lan-online'`.
9. PC sala riceve evento ‚Üí SPA in long-poll su `/events/stream?since=N&event_id=<uuid>` ‚Üí riceve evento immediatamente.
10. Hook `useFileSync` su sala chiama `signLanDownloadUrl({adminBaseUrl, deviceToken, storageKey})` ‚Üí admin firma URL HMAC-SHA256 (scadenza 30 min) ‚Üí sala scarica via `/storage-files/...` con HTTP Range.

